      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "The United States is hardly alone in facing the scourge of terrorism, especially from Iran. Yet, too often, we seem to be alone in our resolve to thwart it.\n\nIf we are serious about “no money for terror,” then there must also be “no room for excuses.”\n\nAt the No Money for Terror conference in Paris, I called on our partners to join @POTUS and the United States in taking action against Iran by designating its financiers, exposing its shell and front companies, shuttering its bank branches, and dismantling its proxies. I urged our partners in the Middle East and Asia to root out Iran’s shadow banking networks.\n\nAs terrorist threats move across borders, our unity of purpose must transcend them as well. Many thanks to Minister @RolandLescure for hosting this important discussion and for inviting me to deliver the keynote address.",
      "text_resolved": "The United States is hardly alone in facing the scourge of terrorism, especially from Iran. Yet, too often, we seem to be alone in our resolve to thwart it.\n\nIf we are serious about “no money for terror,” then there must also be “no room for excuses.”\n\nAt the No Money for Terror conference in Paris, I called on our partners to join @POTUS and the United States in taking action against Iran by designating its financiers, exposing its shell and front companies, shuttering its bank branches, and dismantling its proxies. I urged our partners in the Middle East and Asia to root out Iran’s shadow banking networks.\n\nAs terrorist threats move across borders, our unity of purpose must transcend them as well. Many thanks to Minister @RolandLescure for hosting this important discussion and for inviting me to deliver the keynote address.",
